  <div class="container">

    <div class="card" style="border-left: 8px solid #0277bd;">
      <div class="title">C</div>
      <p>C is one of the oldest and most powerful programming languages. It is widely used in system programming, operating systems, and embedded systems.</p>
      <p><span class="highlight">Uses:</span> OS, compilers, hardware drivers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left: 8px solid #512da8;">
      <div class="title">C++</div>
      <p>C++ is an extension of C with object-oriented features. Known for its performance and flexibility, it's still widely used in game development and high-performance apps.</p>
      <p><span class="highlight">Uses:</span> Games, system software, graphics, real-time apps.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left: 8px solid #f57c00;">
      <div class="title">Java</div>
      <p>Java follows the principle "Write once, run anywhere". It's secure, portable, and used heavily in enterprise applications and Android development.</p>
      <p><span class="highlight">Uses:</span> Android apps, enterprise systems, banking software.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left: 8px solid #4caf50;">
      <div class="title">Python</div>
      <p>Python is popular for its simple syntax and powerful libraries. It's a go-to choice for AI, machine learning, and automation.</p>
      <p><span class="highlight">Uses:</span> AI, ML, data science, web dev, automation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left: 8px solid #fbc02d;">
      <div class="title">JavaScript</div>
      <p>JavaScript is the language of the web. It makes websites interactive and is now used on both frontend and backend (Node.js).</p>
      <p><span class="highlight">Uses:</span> Web apps, mobile apps, game dev, servers.</p>
    </div>

